## 7 Conclusions

In conclusion, we have presented a technique for direct microstructuring of conjugated polymer films. Once structured a polymer film can be used in a wide variety of devices such as an explosive sensing laser or as data transmitters and receivers in visible light communications. The SIIL process allows devices to take advantage of high diffraction efficiencies at the air interface and also to be made in an easy, one-step scalable manner.

